        "## 5. Load Model with Transformers (alternative to vLLM for DataHub)\n",
        "\n",
        "We load **Qwen3-4B-Thinking-2507** with **INT4 quantization** via BitsAndBytes.  \n",
        "\n",
        "Key parameters:\n",
        "- `load_in_4bit` — quantization strategy of INT4"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "3d43b572",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3d43b572"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import torch\n",
        "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForCausalLM, BitsAndBytesConfig\n",
        "\n",
        "MODEL_ID = \"Qwen/Qwen3-4B-Thinking-2507\"\n",
        "\n",
        "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_ID, trust_remote_code=True)\n",
        "tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n",
        "\n",
        "bnb_config = BitsAndBytesConfig(\n",
        "    load_in_4bit=True,\n",
        "    bnb_4bit_compute_dtype=torch.bfloat16,\n",
        "    bnb_4bit_use_double_quant=True,\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "llm = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n",
        "    MODEL_ID,\n",
        "    trust_remote_code=True,\n",
        "    quantization_config=bnb_config,\n",
        "    device_map=\"auto\",\n",
        ")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "47524a46",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "47524a46"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 6. Generate Responses\n",
        "\n",
        "We format every question into a chat-template prompt, then call `llm.generate()` in one batched pass.  \n",
        "vLLM handles batching and scheduling internally — no manual batching needed."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "598ff90c",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "598ff90c"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Generate with vLLM"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "4915f406",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4915f406"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# # Build prompts for first 5 entries\n",
        "# prompts = []\n",
        "# for item in data[:5]:\n",
        "#     system, user = build_prompt(item[\"question\"], item.get(\"options\"))\n",
        "#     prompt_text = tokenizer.apply_chat_template(\n",
        "#         [{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system},\n",
